# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Docker Build Context — WHITELIST approach
# Only include what the Rust build actually needs.
# Everything else is excluded to keep context < 100MB.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Ignore EVERYTHING by default
*

# Then whitelist only what the build needs:
!src/
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!.env.example
!README.md
!persona.toml.example
!build.rs
